Here is another implied postulate or axiom. “ A hard body may be increased or diminished in size to any extent without losing its hardness.'' Empirically, this is untrue. A body which resists all change of form cannot in practice be expanded or contracted ad libitam. To assume it as imaginably true is to assume an axiom‚ not a definition.
